main event: Observers reported seeing an oval object in the sky near Frankfurt, Germany between March 20-25, 1961.
interesting points: The object changed color as it moved in the sky., Observers watched it for approximately 15 seconds before it disappeared., An aircraft intercepted the object., One witness used binoculars to observe the object closely., The object appeared to gain speed rapidly before vanishing.
sighted object: oval object changing color in the sky
witness description: The witness used binoculars and described the object as round with a bright light that moved erratically.
